      "note_no": "110",
      "note": "Three words are used in the Qur'an, with a meaning akin to \"forgive\", but each with a different shade of meaning. 'Afa (here translated \"forgive\") means to forget, to obliterate from one's mind. Safaha (here translated \"overlook\") means to turn away from, to ignore, to treat a matter as if it did not affect one. Ghafara (which does not occur in this verse) means to cover up something as Allah does to our sins with His grace: this word is particularly appropriate in Allah's attribute to Ghaffar. the One who forgives again and again."
